* Electron version: 1.7.5
* Operating system: Debian 9.1

Looks like single instance behavior is broken on linux:
```
const electron = require('electron');
const app = electron.app;

let mainWindow;

const isSecondInstance = app.makeSingleInstance((commandLine, workingDirectory) => {
    // this code is never calls now
    mainWindow.show();
    mainWindow.focus();
    return true;
});

// isSecondInstance is always false here
if (isSecondInstance) {
    app.quit();
}

// creating of mainWindow and some other code
...
```

On Windows 10 this code working just fine
